[SN]TITLE[SN]
Iffy Allen: Former Wrexham winger signs for Bromley

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Bromley have signed winger Iffy Allen following his departure from National League rivals Wrexham.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Allen joined Wrexham in March on a deal until the end of the season, having left Aldershot in December.
The 23-year-old made seven league appearances for the Welsh side before being released on 1 May.
Meanwhile, former Staines Town and Welling winger Luke Wanadio, 24, has also joined the club after leaving National League South side Dartford.
Details of the length of Allen and Wanadio's contracts with Bromley have not been disclosed.
